Extract CShapes data and matrix

Source: R/extract_cshapes.R
extract_cshapes.Rd

Functions to import CShapes 2.0 datasets and distances from the [cShapes] package and format them to a qVerse consistent output for creating maps.

import_cshapes(date, ...)

import_distlist(date, type, ...)

import_distmatrix(date, type, ...)

Arguments

date

The date for which the distance list should be computed. This argument must be of type Date and must be in the range 1/1/1886 - end of the dataset.
...

Arguments to be passed to [cshapes] functions. See the [cshapes] documentation for more details
type

Specifies the type of distance list: "capdist" for capital distances, "centdist" for centroid distances, and "mindist" for minimum distances.

Value

A dataframe with the qVerse-consistently formatted [cshapes] dataset.

A dataframe with the desired distance list between polygons, capitals, or polygon centroids in kilometers.

A matrix with the desired distance list between polygons, capitals, or polygon centroids in kilometers.

Details

import_cshapes()imports CShapes 2.0 datasets and formats them to a qVerse consistent output.

import_distlist() imports pre-computed minimum distance dataframe from the [cShapes] package. Minimum distances are computed in three ways: distances between capitals, distances between centroids of the polygons, minimum distances between the polygons in kilometers.

import_distlist() imports and formats pre-computed minimum distance matrix from the [cShapes] package. Minimum distances are computed in three ways: distances between capitals, distances between centroids of the polygons, minimum distances between the polygons in kilometers.

# \donttest{
import_cshapes(date = "1900-01-01")
